		Expected behavior I expect to be able to create a new account and upload a Gravatar for that account. Actual behavior I am able to create a new account starting with a capital letter (e.g. Example@example.com), and when I then try to upload a Gravatar I get the error Error updating your Gravatar. The activity log shows this error: Network call unsuccessful trying to upload Gravatar: {
"errors": {
"error": "Invalid account address"
}
}
 I can't fix the capital letter through the app or the web, since changing from a capital letter to a lowercase letter isn't seen as a change of address. Support staff has to fix the email address to all lowercase letters, and then the Gravatar can be uploaded as expected. Steps to reproduce the behavior In the app, create a new account with a capital letter at the beginning of the email address (e.g. Example@example.com) On the Me tab, tap the Gravatar icon Select a photo, make any edits (crop/zoom), and tap the checkmark to use it Result: The Gravatar isn't uploaded and there is an error message Error updating your Gravatar Go to Account Settings Tap on "Email address" Change the capital letter in the email address to a lowercase letter and tap OK Result: The change is not saved (the email address with the capital letter remains) Change the account's email address to all lowercase from the network admin Open the app again and try to upload a Gravatar Result: The Gravatar is uploaded as expected. Screenshot Tested on Nexus 9, Android 7.0, WPAndroid alpha-24

